  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>I've had a chat with paulproteus on IRC, and it's awesome to 
get feedback on issues with him there! bd

So, what we have decided is:

1. We'd love a login drop-down from the main openhatch login 
link...
<a href="http://uxmovement.com/forms/dropdown-login-boxes-for-faster-">http://uxmovement.com/forms/dropdown-login-boxes-for-faster-</a>
login

2. That we should have a off-site login page that will contain 
exactly the same content like...
<a href="http://gawker.zendesk.com/access/unauthenticated?return_to=http">http://gawker.zendesk.com/access/unauthenticated?return_to=http</a>
%3A%2F%2Fgawker.zendesk.com%2Flogin

3. Dropdowns are ugly and less comfortable than buttons &amp; tabs.

4. Sign-up and login pages are exactly the same, so merge 
them. - 
        a. If you have an account already then you have the 
option to add / merge that new login type with a your current 
openhatch account.
        b. If you don't have an account already then using 
whatever login type will create a new openhatch account.
        c. Things to validate duplicate users should be 
location or username, and you can't login using another login 
type that has been already been used with an existing account. 
(need more suggestions...)

so I will get a couple of mockups together...
A) for on-site drop-down login 
B) For off-site (Roundup &amp; wiki)

And I think we can still do a cool throbber to show whilst 
sign up / login happens - something spunky, that shows that 
how OpenHatch is so awesome.</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
 
