  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>This is a low-priority UI bug, imho. Go to <a href="http://openhatch.org/account/login/">http://openhatch.org/account/login/</a> 
and click "login with a password". Now click "login with OpenID".

When you click on these links, the bolded link at the top of the "Relatedly" 
section changes. This aspect of the UI accidentally matches a traditional design 
pattern: "vertical list of links, one link bolded". In this pattern the bold 
link indicates the currently selected page. (We use this pattern in the account 
settings pages.) The login pages seem to be mimicking this pattern and in so 
doing mislead me.</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
